public class welcomemessage {
	public void welcomemessage(String name) {
		System.out.println("Hello " + name);
	}

}
/*welcomemessage is the class name. It is not the main class
 * no static - happens when a method/object is accessible using .Object
*make string variable, called name.
*within () is the argument. argument = type of data a method can receive. Extra info the method needs to run. 
*normally (String[] args) is used. String = a group of characters. e.g using system.out.println prints a number of characters.
*This means the method expects an array of strings.
*/
 
